### 7. Integration Patterns: How Systems Interconnect

#### **Pattern A: Cancellation Token Hooks into Disposable Events**

```
CancellationToken.onCancellationRequested()
    ↓
    returns IDisposable
    ↓
    can be stored in DisposableStore
    ↓
    auto-cleaned when store disposes
```

#### **Pattern B: Event Listeners Return Disposables**

```
event(listener) → IDisposable (subscription)
    ↓
    can be added to DisposableStore
    ↓
    fire() automatically delivers to all listeners
    ↓
    dispose() removes listener immediately
```

#### **Pattern C: Async Composition with Lifecycle**

```
createCancelablePromise(callback) → CancelablePromise<T>
    ↓
    callback receives CancellationToken
    ↓
    token.onCancellationRequested() → IDisposable subscription
    ↓
    subscription disposed on settlement (resolve/reject)
    ↓
    if T implements IDisposable: T.dispose() called
```

#### **Pattern D: Event Decorators with Lifecycle Binding**

```
Event.debounce/throttle/buffer(sourceEvent, disposable?)
    ↓
    creates new Emitter<T>
    ↓
    Emitter constructor calls onWillAddFirstListener → subscribe to source
    ↓
    when last listener removed → onDidRemoveLastListener → unsubscribe
    ↓
    if disposable provided: add(emitter) for cleanup
```

#### **Pattern E: Queuing with Cancellation**

```
Throttler/Delayer/ResourceQueue
    ↓
    uses CancellationTokenSource internally
    ↓
    passes token to queued tasks
    ↓
    dispose() cancels source
    ↓
    tasks can check token.isCancellationRequested
```

